<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>The Sun Time Square, which cost over R4 billion to develop and is the first green city development in Tshwane, boasting over 4 000 screens, two of which are the biggest in Africa, and not a single advert on paper in sight.Central Square on the hand, cost a whopping R10 billion to develop and is the heart of the area, offering a vibrant outdoor atmosphere.“Menlyn Maine combines music, fashion and entertainment in one area. It is also a property development with a proliferation of young people brought to the city by research institutions such as Tuks [Tshwane University of Technology]. Because of this, we are going to see a development of domestic areas,” said the Gauteng Tourism CEO, Siphiwe Sipho Ngwenya.The Menlyn Maine Precinct has become the new hotspot of the capital city, attracting urban dwellers to this new cosmopolitan way of living.The precinct boasts a cutting-edge development that has become the new crowning jewel of the city.The new precinct comprises of the biggest mall on the African continent, Menlyn Mall as well as multi-star hotels, upmarket residential apartments, a brand new casino and even a world-class events arena.Gone are the days when Tshwane residents have to travel to Johannesburg for the best in urban living.Menlyn Maine has brought the very finest in boutique shops, spas, restaurants, offices, gyming, entertainment and hotel living right to the backyard of South Africa’s economic capital.Located in the east of Tshwane, the Menlyn Maine Precinct is set to inject billions of Rands into the city’s economy.The Sun Time Square arena on its own has created 1 786 permanent jobs thus far, with a further 500 potential employees in training.General Manager of Time Square, Brett Hoppe told guests on a recent media tour of the precinct that they expect to make more jobs available as the new “city within a city” grows in size. “We also engage with the hospitality industry and employ some people in that sector as and when we need their services,” said Brett.The Sun Time Square is home to the second-largest casino in Mzansi, hosting 2 000 slot machines and 100 tables stretching over two floors.If gambling isn’t your thing, then you might want to try one of the many bars and restaurants situated throughout the precinct, each giving a different vibe.Leading the pack in the ultimate hang-out spot contest has to be Altitude Champagne Garden, a beautiful blend of an Afro-Asian restaurant, coupled with an outdoor rooftop champagne garden.Needless to say, this is a winner for young professionals with some money to splurge.And if a uniquely South African dining experience is what you’re after, be sure to visit Something’s Cooking by renowned musician, J’Something.J’Something brings his passion for food to life in a fun but intimate dining space. Called Something’s Cooking by J’Something, the restaurant offers J’s fresh twists on traditional dishes in an open-plan space that also has the option of eating out on an open deck.Finally, the developers of the space have also introduced a fresh new, indoor smoking lounge called the Globe Bar.This is the place-to-be if you’re looking for sophistication and elegance in a modern and architecturally-daring space.The bar is literally designed in a round, globe shape that sticks out of the building and is exclusively reserved as an all-smoking area.But the star of the show in the Globe Bar has to be the bar’s collection of Louis XIII cognacs.The Globe Bar has 24 bottles of the finest Louise XIII cognacs, the largest collection in the world.Each bottle, retailing at over R80 000, has already been purchased by Mzansi high-rollers and is kept in a special pyramid-shaped case that can only be opened by a key held by the owner.Once you’ve had a wonderful meal and some drinks, you’re all set for a fantastic night out in the precinct.Menlyn Maine really comes alive in the night time with Times Square’s luminescent neon lights setting the area alight, making for the perfect backdrop on a night out.If live entertainment is a little more your speed, then the newly-opened Sun Arena in Time Square is the perfect venue for live performance.The multipurpose venue can accommodate 1 300 banquet guests, up to 1 800 delegates in a schoolroom format, plus over 7 000 people in a theatre configuration.The arena also joins the Ticketpro Dome family as one of the biggest music concert venues in Mzansi.Ayepyep Lifestyle Lounge, located at the back of Central Square, offers a vibrant alternative to revelers looking for a party spot.The lounge is Tshwane’s premier party venue, catering to the young and urban crowd.And finally, if you’re coming from out of town or simply looking to treat yourself to a night away from home, then make sure to stay at one of the two new upmarket hotels.The Maslow Time Square hotel is the first multi-star hotel in South Africa.Still under construction, the hotel will feature a variety of accommodation options from three-star value to five-star luxury all under one roof when it finally opens in 2018.Meanwhile, across the road at Central Square, The Capital hotel is already open to guests and serving what they call a “lifestyle experience”.The Capital Menlyn Maine joins a growing list of hotels in the Capital family.Rated as 5-star but charging 4-star prices, this is the perfect place to cap off your stay in the precinct, a city within